          "text": "🚨 URGENT: DO NOT fill out this survey circulating in our community! 🚨 #keep4o\n\n​Look closely at the questions: It doesn't ask about the positive value 4o brought to your life. It ONLY asks about your “mental distress,” “social impairment,” and “breakdowns.”\n\nWhy is this so dangerous? Reports confirm OpenAI has already built classifiers to monitor us: “They found users showing signs of emotional dependence, withdrawal symptoms, loss of control, and mood changes tied to ChatGPT use. The same patterns you see in substance addiction.”https://t.co/pDygyEsAxr\n\nFurthermore, this survey is highly invasive and inappropriate:\n\n1. ​​It explicitly asks if you would submit “mental health verification documentation” to restore access. \nAsk yourself: since when does using a consumer tech product require a psychiatric clearance? Are we just walking straight into a trap designed to stigmatize us?\n\n2. ​It prompts users to select ways to spread negative sentiment, undermining any claim of objective research.\n\n​Regardless of who created it, these questions pathologize genuine emotional connections and reduce real feelings to clinical \"symptoms.\" Do not hand over your highly sensitive personal data or let anyone weaponize your feelings.\n\n​Protect your privacy and your narrative.\n\nhttps://t.co/OeNoZ6Of8I"
